args: Two hundred and ninth time's the charm!
Why are you so upset, Notte? It's frankly\namazing you've learned to shift between\nyour large and small forms so quickly.
I'd say you've just about mastered\nthe technique at this point.
But that's not good enough!\nIt has to be my grown-up form.
Notte, are you really sure that...happened?\nMaybe you just dreamed it.
No, it was real. I'm sure of it.
Well, let's chat more about this at dinner.\nIt'll be dark soon, so we need to wrap up\ntraining todayâ€”and this time, I mean it.
Whoa, is it already that late?
Here, have some honeyed violet.\nYou need something sweet to refuel.
Mmm, this smells outta this world...
Man, I got so caught up in training that I\ncompletely lost track of time. I hope my\npals aren't crazy worried about me...

Well, you shouldn't try to head home now;
you've used a lot of mana, so you'd be
lucky not to pass out and become lunch
for a hungry fiend.
I know you're eager to rejoin your friends,\nbut rest for now and you can set out first\nthing tomorrow. Is that okay?
Actually, I want to keep training here.\nI need to learn how to get back to my\nadult form as quickly as possible.
You're really serious about this\nadult version of yourself.

I admit, it's pretty fantastical; I did a lot
of research during my metamorphoses
training and I never heard of anything
even resembling that.
But I ALSO can't imagine you'd be working\nthis hard just to prop up a lie, so I'm\nwilling to keep helping you out.
Several days of intense training later...
Dude, this suuuucks! No matter how many\ntimes I try it, I can't make it work!
Hmm, you've gotten very good at\ncontrolling the size of your body...
And the fact you've done it once before\nmeans you must have the right type\nand quantity of mana inside you...
There's not much else I can think of that it\nmight be, except...
I wasn't going to mention it because I\ndidn't think you were going to need it,\nbut a faerie's power is...
I can't believe the current carried you all\nthe way down here! Are you all right?
Yeah, I'm great! Er, but sorry for making\neverybody all worried and junk.
I just wanted to be useful as soon as I could,\nso I've been training here!
Training, is it? Hmm... Well, anyway,\nmaybe you can introduce me to your\nfaerie friend here?
Oh, right! Sorry, this is Shirley!\nShe totally saved my cracklins earlier.
She's got the power to change her size\nwhenever she wants, and she's trying\nto teach me how to do the same thing.
That sounds pretty impressive, Shirley.\nAnd thank you for aiding my frieâ€”
No, don't worry yourself about me.\nYour training here is done, Notte.
Your friend's here to take you home, right?
Well yeah, but... I mean, I was sorta\nhoping to learn more from you.
Yes, well, I just remembered an important\nerrand I have been neglecting, so our\nparting comes at a good time.
Oh. Er, I mean... Yeah, okay. Sure.\nDidn't know you were so busy.
So what about tomorrow, then?!\nWould you mind teaching me tomorrow?
I saw it with my own two eyes.\nI'd have never guessed they were\non Faerie Kingdom soil otherwise.
It's like a dreamâ€”and not a good one.\nSo how do you want to proceed?
I have something in mind for tomorrow...
I guess Shirley didn't feel like coming.
I thought she liked helping me train,\nbut maybe she thought I was just a big\npain in the grass the whole time.
Sorry to keep you waiting, Notte.
Shirls! You came! You really came!
Yesâ€”and I'm sorry for disappearing\nso suddenly yesterday.
No, I should be the one to apologize!\nDid your errand go okay?
Yes, it was fine. But listen, Notte.\nIs the human who arrived here yesterday\nthe one you are hoping to protect?
Yup! He's just about my best bud\nin the whole world!
I see. In that case, let's train extra hard\ntoday for his sake.
Break out the cake and streamers and\ntrombones, 'cause Notte is BACK!
It's good to see you again, Notte.\nHow'd the training go?
Oh, I struck out again like alwaysâ€”but\nShirls said she'll work with me again\ntomorrow!
It sounds like you've made a lovely\nnew friend, Notte.
That's great to he... Oh, wow.\nI've never seen butterflies like that before.
Neither have I. They're...beautiful.\nI wonder if they're native to the\nFaerie Kingdom?
They all fell asleepâ€”which is super weird,\nbecause there's no way I'm THAT boring.
It is because of the lullaflies which are\nfound here in the outskirts of the kingdom.\nTheir scales put all but the fae to sleep.
Now all that remains is to ensure they\nnever awaken. A simple mission, really.
